  line 3
  line `THE INDO - TIBETAN BORDER POLICE FORCE ACT, 1992`
  line _______
  line `ARRA N GE N MENT OF SECTIONS`
  line _______
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `1. Short title and commencement.`
  line `2. Definitions.`
  line `3. Persons subject to this Act.`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `C ONSTITUTION OF THE F ORCE AND CONDITIONS OR SERVICE OF THE MEMBERS OF THE F ORCE`
  line `4. Constitution of the Force.`
  line `5. Control, direction, etc.`
  line `6. Enrolment.`
  line `7. Liability for service outside India.`
  line `8. Resignation and withdrawal from the post.`
  line `9. Tenure of service under the Act.`
  line `10. Termination of service by Central Government.`
  line `11. Dismissal, removal or reduction by the Director - General and by other officers.`
  line `12. Certificate of termination of service.`
  line `13. Restrictions respecting right to form association, freedom of speech, etc.`
  line `14. Remedy of aggrieved persons other than officers.`
  line `15. Remedy of aggrieved officers.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `O FFENCES`
  line `16. Offences in relation to the enemy or terrorist and punishable with death.`
  line `17. Offences in relation to the enemy and not punishable with death.`
  line `18. Offences punishable more severely on active duty than at other times.`
  line `19. Mutiny.`
  line `20. Desertion and aiding desertion.`
  line `21. Absence without leave.`
  line `22. Striking or threatening superior officers.`
  line `23. Disobedience to superior officer.`
  line `24. Insubordination an d obstruction.`
  line `25. False answers on enrolment.`
  line `26. Unbecoming conduct.`
  line `27. Certain forms of disgraceful conduct.`
  line `28. Ill - treating a subordinate.`
  line `29. Intoxication.`
  line `30. Permitting escape of person in custody.`
  line `31. Irregularity in connection with arrest or confinement.`
  line `32. Escape from custody.`
  line `33. Offences in respect of property.`
  line `34. Extortion and exaction.`
  line `35. Making away with equipment.`
  line `36. Injury to property.`
