  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `37. False accusations.`
  line `38. Falsifying official documents and false declarations.`
  line `39. Signing in blank and failure to report.`
  line `40. Offences relating to Force Court.`
  line `41. False evidence.`
  line `42. Unlawful detention of pay.`
  line `43. Violation of good order and discipline.`
  line `44. Miscellaneous offences.`
  line `45. Attempt.`
  line `46. Abetment of offences that have been committed.`
  line `47. Abetment of offences punishable with death and not c ommitte d.`
  line `48. Abetment of offences punishable with imprisonment and not committed.`
  line `49. Civil offences.`
  line `50. Civil offences not triable by a Force Court.`
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `P UNISHMENTS`
  line `51. Punishment awardable by Force Courts.`
  line `52. Alternative punishments awardable by Force Courts.`
  line `53. Combination of punishment s.`
  line `54. Retention in the f orce of a person convicted on active duty.`
  line `55. Punishments otherwise than by Force Courts.`
  line `56. Minor punishments.`
  line `57. Limit of punishments under section 56.`
  line `58. Punishment of persons of or below the rank of Commandant by Inspectors - General and others.`
  line `59. Review of proceedings.`
  line `60. Collective fines.`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `D EDUCTIONS FROM PAY AND ALLOWANCES`
  line `61. Deductions from pay and allowances of persons subject to this Act.`
  line `62. Pay and allowances during trial.`
  line `63. Limit of certain deductions.`
  line `64. Deduction from public money due to a person.`
  line `65. Pay and allowances of prisoner of war during inquiry into his conduct.`
  line `66. Remission of deduction s.`
  line `67. Provision for dependants of prisoner of war from his remitted deduction s and pay and`
  line allowances.
  line `68. Period during which a person is de e dmed to be a prisoner of war.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `A RREST AND PROCEEDINGS BEFORE TRIAL`
  line `69. Custody of offenders.`
  line `70. Duty of commanding office r in regard to detention.`
  line `71. Interval between committal and trial.`
  line `72. Arrest by civil authorities.`
  line `73. Capture of deserters.`
  line `74. Inquiry into absence without leave.`
  line `75. Force Police Officers.`
