obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `THE INDO - TIBETAN BORDER POLICE FORCE ACT, 1992`
  line `A CT N O. 35 OF 1992`
  line `[1 st September, 1992. ]`
  line `An Act to provide for the constitution and regulation of an armed force of the Union for ensuring`
  line `the security of the borders of India a nd for matters connected therewith.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Forty - third Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short title and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Indo - Tibetan Border Police`
  line `Force Act, 1992.`
  line `( 2 ) It shall come into force on such date 1 as the Central Government may, by notific ation, appoint.`
  line `2. Definitions. — ( 1 ) In this Act, unless t he context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “active duty”, in relation to a person subject to this Act, means any duty as a member of the`
  line `Force during the period in which such person is attached to, or form s part of, a unit of the Force —`
  line `( i ) which is engaged in operations against an enemy, or`
  line `( ii ) which is operating at a picket or engaged on patrol or other guard d uty along the borders`
  line `of India,`
  line `and includes duty by such person during any period declared by the Central Government by order as a`
  line `period of active duty with reference to any area in which any person or class of persons subject to this Act`
  line `may be serving;`
  line `( b ) “battalion” means a unit of the Force constituted as a batta lion by the Central Government;`
  line `( c ) “civil offence” means an offence which is triable by a criminal court;`
  line `( d ) “civil prison” means any jail or place used for the detention of any criminal prisoner under the`
  line `Prisons Act, 1894 (9 of 1894), or under any other law for the time being in force;`
  line `( e ) “ com manding officer”, used in relation to a person subject to this Act, means an officer for the`
  line `time being in command of the unit or any separate portion of the Force to which such person belongs`
  line `or is attached;`
  line `( f ) “criminal court” means a court of ordinary criminal justice in an y part of India and includes a`
  line `C ourt of a special Judge appointed under the Criminal Law Am endment Act, 1952 (46 of 1952);`
  line `( g ) “Deputy Inspector - General” and “ Addi tional Deputy Inspector - General” mean respectively a`
  line `Deputy Inspector - General and an Additional Deputy Inspector - General of the Force appointed under`
  line `secti on 5;`
  line `( h ) “Director - General” and “Additional Director - General” mean respectively the`
  line `Director - General and an Additional Director - General of the Force appointed under section 5;`
  line `( i ) “enemy” includes all armed mutineers, armed rebels, armed rioters, pirates and any person in`
  line `arms against whom it is the duty of any person subj ect to this Act to take action;`
  line `( j ) “enrolled person” means an under - officer or other person enrolled und er this Act;`
  line `( k ) “Force” means the In do - Tibetan Border Police Force;`
  line `( l ) “Force Court” means a C ourt referred to in section 76;`
  line `( m ) “Force custody” means the arrest or confinement of a member of the Force according t o`
  line rules;
  line `( n ) “Inspector - General” means the Inspector - General of the F orce appointed under section 5;`
  line `1. 30th May, 1994, vide Notifn. No. S.O. 414(E), dated 28th May, 1994, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3( ii ).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
