  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `( o ) “ Ju dge Attorney - General”, “Additional Judge Attorney - General”, “ Deputy Judge`
  line `Attorney - General” and “ J udge Attorney” mean respectively the Judge Attorney - General, an`
  line `Additional Judge Attorney - General, a Deputy Judge Attorney - General and a Judge Attorney of the`
  line `Force appointed in the appropriate rank by the Central Government;`
  line `( p ) “member of the Force” means an officer, a subordinate officer, an under - of ficer or other`
  line `enrolled person;`
  line `( q ) “ notif ication” means a notification pub lished in the Official Gazette;`
  line `( r ) “offence” means any act or omission punishable under this Act and include s a civil offence;`
  line `( s ) “officer” means a person appointed or in pay as an officer of the Force, but does not include a`
  line `subordina te officer or an under - officer;`
  line `( t ) “prescribed” means prescribe d by rules made under this Act;`
  line `( u ) “rule” me ans a rule made under this Act;`
  line `( v ) “subordinate officer” means a person appointed or in pay as a Subedar Major, a Subedar or a`
  line `Sub - I nspector of the Force;`
  line `( w ) “superior officer”, when used in relation to a per son subject to this Act, means —`
  line `( i ) any member of the Force to whose command such person is for the time being subjec t in`
  line `accordance with the rules;`
  line `( ii ) any officer of a higher rank or class or of a higher grade in the same class,`
  line `and includes, when such person is not an officer, a s ubordinate officer or an under - officer of a higher`
  line `rank, class or grade;`
  line `( x ) “under - officer” means a Head Constable, a Naik or a Lance Naik of t he Force;`
  line `( y ) “unit” includes —`
  line `( a ) any body of officers and other members of the Force for which a separate a uthorised`
  line `establishment exists;`
  line `( b ) any separate body of persons subject to this Act employed on any service and not attached`
  line `to a unit as aforesa id;`
  line `( c ) any other separate body of persons composed wholly or partly of persons subject to this`
  line `Act and specified as a unit by the Central Government;`
  line `( z ) all words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860), the Army Act, 1950 (4 5 of 1950) or the National Security Guard Act, 1986 (47 of`
  line `1986), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to t hem in that Code or those Acts.`
  line `( 2 ) In this Act, references to any law not in force in the State of Jammu and Kashmir * shall be`
  line `construed as references to the correspond ing law in force in that State.`
  line `3. Persons subject to this Act. — ( 1 ) The following persons appointed (whether on deputation or in`
  line `any other manner) in the Force shall be subject to this Act, wherever they may be, namely: —`
  line `( a ) officer s and subordinate officers; and`
  line `( b ) under - officers and other p ersons enrolled under this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Every person subject to this Act shall remain so subject until repatriated, retired, released,`
  line `discharged, removed or dismissed from the Force in accordance with the provis ions of this Act and the`
  line rules.
  line `*. Vide N otifn. No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  kind page
